# Needle in Haystack Context Test
# This script tests each model's ability to find a unique key in a large text body

# Configuration
set model1 = "prism_bonsai"
set model2 = "mistral_1"
set judge_model = "mistral_1"
set output_dir = "haystack_test_actual"
set hay_key = "hay_key: 8081C452-F5C9-4938-A00A-EB91A0DA71D3"

# Haystack text - 10000 words with the hay_key embedded
set haystack_text = "The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog. This sentence contains all letters of the alphabet. Programming is a fascinating field that requires both creativity and logical thinking. Artificial intelligence has made significant strides in recent years with models becoming increasingly capable. Machine learning algorithms can process vast amounts of data to find patterns that humans might miss. The development of neural networks has revolutionized how we approach complex problems. Deep learning models with many layers can learn hierarchical representations of data. Natural language processing allows computers to understand and generate human text. The transformer architecture introduced attention mechanisms that greatly improved model performance. Large language models are trained on massive datasets containing billions of tokens. The ability to generate coherent and contextually appropriate text is a hallmark of modern AI systems. Fine tuning on specific tasks can adapt a general model to specialized domains. Reinforcement learning from human feedback helps align model outputs with human preferences. The field of AI ethics explores the moral implications of intelligent systems. Bias in training data can lead to biased outputs from machine learning models. Fairness and transparency are important considerations in AI development. Explainable AI aims to make model decisions understandable to humans. The intersection of AI and healthcare offers promising applications for diagnosis and treatment. Computer vision enables machines to interpret and understand visual information from the world. Image classification tasks have achieved superhuman performance on many benchmarks. Object detection identifies and locates multiple objects within an image. Segmentation divides an image into meaningful regions or categories. Speech recognition converts audio signals into written text. Text to speech systems generate spoken language from written text. Machine tr